title: Some more rare astrology,palmistry and occult books
description:
1)jataka tatva by V.SUBRAHMANYA SHASTRI printed in 1941

jataka tatva (eng trans: "the philosophy of horoscope") this is one of the classics in vedic astrology by the veteran 
translator.irony is translator wasn't a professional astrologer nor a student of it but translation is so excellent that 
even a expert can't be so good!

2)MOHINI VIDYA SADHANA AND SIDDHI BY A.L.BHAGWAT PRINTED IN 1975

ONE OF THE BEST, RAREST,GREAT (WHATEVER U MAY CALL IT)BOOK I'VE COME ACROSS.BESIDES ITS SIMPLE EXPLAINATION IT ALSO GIVES A SERIES OF EXERCISE IN GAZING AND WHAT NOT!.
I STRONGLY RECOMMEND THAT ONE SHOULD ATLEAST TRY SOME EXERCISES AND B SURE THAT U WILL COME ACROSS THAT XTRA SENSE OR 6TH
SENSE WHICH PPL REFER TO.
I'LL UPLOAD EXERCISE CHARTS DESIGNED BY ME BASED ON THE DETAILS PROVIDED IN THE BOOK
ENJOY!

3)Science of palmistry by M.A.DEVACHARYA date unknown but not that old

one of the good palmistry books based on research

4)TETRABIBLIOS BY PTOLEMY PRINTED IN 1882

this is something like an aphorisms i feel try it out and say if it works perfectly!

5)choice aphorisms from 7 segments of cardan edited by william lilly in 1675

aphorisms related to nativity,accident and general queries answered according to astrological principles

6)christian astrology by william lilly

of course this is like a classic in western astrology
